exports[`default environment argument parameter name prefix > when both argument CLI_PARAM and CLI_PARAMETER are passed then an error is thrown 1`] = `
[
  [
    "Cannot run command, you made some mistakes:

The parameter "foo" was passed an argument multiple times via different parameter aliases in the environment.

Here are the docs for this command:


PARAMETERS

  Name    Type      Default      Environment (1)  
                                                  
  foo     string     REQUIRED    ✓                
                                                  
         
  NOTES  
  ━━━━━  
  (1) Parameters can be passed arguments via environment variables. Command  
      line arguments take precedence. Environment variable names are snake   
      cased versions of the parameter name (or its aliases), case            
      insensitive. They must be prefixed with CLI_PARAMETER_ or CLI_PARAM_   
      (case insensitive). Examples:                                          
      → CLI_PARAMETER_FOO="..."                                              
",
  ],
]
`;

